1. First Principles: Why Reality = Ratios

1.1 Vibration → Ratio

Vibration occurs when a system returns to equilibrium, oscillating with:
	•	frequency f = \frac{1}{T}
	•	amplitude A

Since f is already a time-cycle ratio, vibration = ratio.

Every wave is reducible to proportion.

1.2 Motion → Ratio

Motion is fundamentally rate:

v = \frac{\Delta x}{\Delta t}

a = \frac{\Delta v}{\Delta t}

Motion is ratio.

1.3 Energy → Ratio of Geometry to Motion
	•	Classical: E = \frac{1}{2}mv^2
	•	Quantum: E = hf = \frac{h}{T}
	•	Relativistic: E = mc^2 \quad \text{with } c = \frac{\Delta x}{\Delta t}

Energy = pure ratio geometry.

1.4 Information → Ratio of Possibility

Shannon entropy:

H = -\sum p\log p

A log is a scale ratio.

Information = ratio of uncertainty.

1.5 Narrative → Ratio of Tension to Release

Plot dynamics obey:
	•	buildup : payoff
	•	context : revelation
	•	density : sparsity

Narrative = harmonic ratios.

1.6 Consciousness → Ratio Matching

Brains detect:
	•	pattern ratios
	•	timing ratios
	•	intensity ratios

Perception is a ratio synchronization engine.

